### Test API Find Account by PolicyNumber

### 1. Test database connection first
GET https://localhost:7001/test-db

### 2. Create schema if needed
POST https://localhost:7001/create-schema

### 3. Check tables
GET https://localhost:7001/check-tables

### 4. Create test account - Controller API
POST https://localhost:7001/api/account
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "policyNumber": "POL001",
    "policyAccountNumber": "ACC001",
    "balance": 1000.50
}

### 5. Create another test account - Minimal API
POST https://localhost:7001/policy-accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "policyNumber": "POL002",
    "policyAccountNumber": "ACC002", 
    "balance": 2000.75
}

### 6. Find account by PolicyNumber - Controller API (RECOMMENDED)
GET https://localhost:7001/api/account/POL001

### 7. Find account by PolicyNumber - Minimal API
GET https://localhost:7001/policy-accounts/POL002

### 8. Test not found case - Controller API
GET https://localhost:7001/api/account/POL999

### 9. Test not found case - Minimal API  
GET https://localhost:7001/policy-accounts/POL999

### 10. Create more test data
POST https://localhost:7001/api/account
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "policyNumber": "POL003",
    "policyAccountNumber": "ACC003",
    "balance": 5000.25
}

### 11. Find the new account
GET https://localhost:7001/api/account/POL003